name: Eyecubes Flamingo
description:
An "eyecube" of Flamingo. The name "flamingo" comes from Portuguese / Spanish flamengo, "flame-colored." Four flamingo species are distributed throughout the Americas, and two are native to Africa, Asia, and Europe. 

/ Eyecubes are the animals of the our virtual spaces. They roam the worlds. They behave differently from human avatars. 
/ Eyecubes are marrying the fading biodiversity of the real world with the potentials of the virtual worlds.
